				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><br />
<b>Prerequisites</b>&#160;: Know how to start Unreal Engine 4 Editor and open a blueprint in blueprint editor. If not please follow Epic's YouTube tutorial.
</p><p><b>Skill Level</b>: Newbie, scrub, noob, just paid subscription to build my dream game. This tutorial assumes you have no prior knowledge in blueprint.
</p><p><b>IMPORTANT</b>: This tutorial is not a Howto for everything you want, it is only here to help you understand blueprint's concept and how it works.
</p>
